docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-27.md:143:- **R1 (Critical, three-reviewer consensus, iter-1 regression of 
C1):** the C1 `ReadOnlyTransactionWorld` denylist was missing 9+ real mutating methods on `World` (`random`, 
`setResourceMax`, `setProduction`, `setConsumption`, `start`, `stop`, `pause`, `resume`, `setSpeed`, `onDestroy`, 
`offDestroy`, `onTickFailure`, `offTickFailure`, `onCommandResult`, `offCommandResult`, `onCommandExecution`, 
`offCommandExecution`) and contained 6 spurious entries (`registerComponentOptions`, `setTickFailureListener`, 
`setCommandResultListener`, `setCommandExecutionListener`, `setOnDestroy`, `rebuildSpatialIndex`). The most damaging 
gap: `random()` mutates `DeterministicRandom.state`, so a side-effecting predicate that called `w.random()` advanced 
the RNG even on `precondition_failed`, **breaking the engine's determinism contract and snapshot-replay correctness**. 
Fix: introduced `FORBIDDEN_PRECONDITION_METHODS` const array as a single source of truth. The type-level `Omit` 
derives from `(typeof FORBIDDEN_PRECONDITION_METHODS)[number]`; the runtime `Set` derives from the same array. Drift 
between the two lists is now impossible by construction. Added a property-based regression test that iterates the 
array and asserts every method throws when called from a precondition; explicit tests pin the headline cases 
(`random()`, `setProduction`, lifecycle methods).
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-27.md:409:- `src/version.ts`: new file exporting `ENGINE_VERSION = '0.7.6' as 
const`. Will be read by `SessionRecorder` / `scenarioResultToBundle()` for `metadata.engineVersion`. Avoids 
`process.env.npm_package_version` (only set under `npm run`).
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-27.md:411:- `src/world.ts` (T0.4 plan step): added public 
`applySnapshot(snapshot)` instance method. Implementation: creates a fresh world via `World.deserialize(snapshot)`, 
then transfers state-bearing private fields (entityManager, componentStores, componentOptions, componentBits, 
nextComponentBit, entitySignatures, spatialGrid, previousPositions, resourceStore, rng, stateStore + state*, 
entityTags + tagIndex, entityMeta + metaIndex, *DirtyEntities) into `this`. Preserves user-registered 
handlers/validators/systems/listeners and the `__payloadCapturingRecorder` slot. Resets `currentDiff`/`currentMetrics`/
`activeMetrics`/`queryCache`/`lastTickFailure`/`poisoned`/`commandQueue`/`resolvedSystemOrder`. Calls `recover()` 
first if poisoned.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-27.md:412:- `src/command-transaction.ts`: added `'applySnapshot'` to 
`FORBIDDEN_PRECONDITION_METHODS` so a transaction predicate cannot bulk-mutate via it (matches the existing 
C1/R1/iter-2/iter-3 denylist discipline).
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-27.md:413:- `tests/world-applysnapshot.test.ts`: new file with 6 tests 
covering state copy, tick replacement, entity manager overwrite, system preservation, `isCurrent` after applySnapshot, 
cached-diff cleanup.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-27.md:419:- `World.applySnapshot` resolves the iter-3 worldFactory 
replay-construction problem: `World.deserialize` returns a fresh World without user registrations, but 
`setupScenario(w)` after deserialize would conflict (`registerComponent` / `registerHandler` throw on duplicate). With 
`applySnapshot`, the worldFactory pattern becomes register-first-then-apply-snapshot.
docs\devlog\detailed\2026-04-26_2026-04-27.md:425:- `World.applySnapshot` re-uses `World.deserialize` internally 
rather than duplicating the snapshot-loading logic - keeps a single source of truth for snapshot validation/loading.
