docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3714:### ADR 1: Separate `SessionRecorder` 
rather than extend `WorldHistoryRecorder`
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3716:**Decision:** Introduce `SessionRecorder` 
as a new primitive alongside `WorldHistoryRecorder`. Do not extend the existing recorder.
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3718:**Context:** `WorldHistoryRecorder` is an 
in-memory bounded rolling buffer (default capacity 64) with a range-summary helper, designed for runtime debugging and 
AI agent inspection during a live run. Session recording needs unbounded capture, sink-based streaming, marker API, 
and a replayer companion. Two genuinely different use cases.
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3728:- Default-config `WorldHistoryRecorder` (no 
`captureCommandPayloads`) attaches to the same `World` alongside `SessionRecorder` without interference (each 
subscribes independently to listeners; only `SessionRecorder` wraps `submitWithResult`). **Payload-capturing variants 
are mutually exclusive** per A7.1 step 2 ??" only one of `SessionRecorder` or `WorldHistoryRecorder({ 
captureCommandPayloads: true })` may attach to a given world at a time.
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3729:- Future synthetic playtest spec will 
likely use `SessionRecorder` directly, not `WorldHistoryRecorder`.
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3733:**Decision:** `SessionBundle` is exported 
as a strict-JSON shared type and is identical regardless of producer. Both `SessionRecorder.toBundle()` and 
`scenarioResultToBundle()` emit the same shape; `MemorySink.toBundle()` and `FileSink.toBundle()` produce structurally 
equal bundles modulo `attachments[].ref` (dataUrl vs sidecar). Sidecar binary payloads live outside the JSON shape and 
are accessed via `source.readSidecar(id)`. The replayer accepts `SessionBundle` regardless of producer.
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3743:### ADR 3: Determinism contract documented, 
not enforced (in this spec)
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3745:**Decision:** Document user obligations for 
replay determinism. Do not add engine-level enforcement (e.g., a strict-mode flag that rejects external mutations). 
Provide `SessionReplayer.selfCheck()` as the verification mechanism.
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3747:**Context:** Strict-mode enforcement is a 
behaviorally invasive engine-wide change (audit every mutation method, gate on inside-tick state, provide escape 
hatches for setup/deserialize). Conflating it with session recording would make this spec significantly larger and the 
implementation riskier.
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3759:### ADR 4: `worldFactory` is part of the 
determinism contract
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3761:**Decision:** The `worldFactory` callback 
supplied to `SessionReplayer` is part of the determinism contract. Drift between record-time setup and replay-time 
`worldFactory` produces selfCheck divergences indistinguishable from genuine determinism violations in user code.
docs\reviews\session-recording-plan\2026-04-27\3\raw\codex.stderr.log:3788:4. **`ReplayerConfig.worldFactory` 
ergonomics.** Per ADR 4, the factory is part of the determinism contract. A future spec may add a 
registration-manifest shape-check to surface factory drift with a clearer diagnostic; not v1.
