docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\REVIEW.md:1:# Multi-CLI Design Review - Session Recording & Replay 
Spec
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\REVIEW.md:82:**Fix:** add explicit clause to 11.1 determinism 
contract - "do NOT call `world.submit()` from inside any system, command handler, event listener, or other code that 
runs during `world.step()`. All command submissions must originate from outside the tick loop." Make `selfCheck()` 
surface this when it diverges (the divergence will be visible in the command stream count). Future strict-mode spec 
can structurally enforce.
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\REVIEW.md:129:`MemorySink` and `FileSink` both implement `SessionSink 
& SessionSource`. `SessionReplayer.fromSink()` becomes `fromSource()` and accepts the read interface.
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\REVIEW.md:131:### H4. Validators must be in the determinism contract. 
(Codex H5)
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\REVIEW.md:135:### H5. Determinism contract missing engine+Node 
version coupling, transcendentals, registration order, query iteration order. (Opus H3)
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\REVIEW.md:139:- "Replay determinism requires identical engine version 
*and* identical V8 / Node major version. Math transcendentals (`Math.sin`, `Math.cos`, `Math.log`, etc.) are not 
bit-identical across V8 versions; cross-runtime replay may diverge even with all other obligations met. The bundle 
records `metadata.engineVersion`; `SessionReplayer` warns when the runtime engine version differs and refuses 
cross-major-version replay."
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\REVIEW.md:140:- "System and component registration order must match 
between recording and replay. The `worldFactory` is part of the determinism contract."
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\REVIEW.md:213:**Fix:** new ADR 4 in 15: "The `worldFactory` callback 
is part of the determinism contract. Bundle replay requires the consumer to reproduce the recording-time 
component/validator/handler/system registration set, in the same order. Drift between record-time and replay-time 
factories produces `selfCheck` divergences indistinguishable from genuine determinism violations. Acceptable in v1; a 
future spec may persist a registration manifest in the bundle."
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\REVIEW.md:249:**Fix:** 13.3 / 18 acceptance criteria: "Every 
existing scenario in the engine test suite runs `selfCheck()` on its produced bundle as part of `npm test`. selfCheck 
failures fail the test suite. This converts the documented determinism contract into an enforced-by-corpus gate."
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\REVIEW.md:261:7. Determinism contract (11) - mid-tick submit 
forbidden (CR5); validators must be pure (H4); engine+Node version + transcendentals + registration order + query 
iteration (H5); poison/recover replay scope-limited (CR3).
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\raw\codex.md:10:- `fromSink()` and the on-disk format are 
underspecified for replay-critical data. The file layout only streams `ticks.jsonl` plus snapshots/attachments, even 
though replay also needs commands/executions/failures; meanwhile `SessionReplayer.fromSink()` accepts a write-oriented 
`SessionSink` interface that has no read/stream API beyond `toBundle()`, which is incompatible with the claimed lazy 
manifest/JSONL loading. `docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:149-159,258-268,290-293`
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\raw\codex.md:11:- The determinism contract is incomplete because it 
ignores validator-time behavior. `submitWithResult()` runs validators immediately with a live `World`, before the 
command is queued, so "route all input through `world.submit()`" is not enough unless validators are also required to 
be deterministic and side-effect free. As written, a user can follow 11 and still create uncaptured out-of-tick 
mutations. `docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:396-408`; `src/world.ts:728-757,760-766`
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\raw\codex.md:24:- ADR 1, keeping session recording separate from 
`WorldHistoryRecorder`, is defensible. The spec's main weaknesses are elsewhere: the bundle is missing replay-grade 
inputs, the sink boundary does not match the engine's listener semantics, and the "documented, not enforced" 
determinism story depends on a `selfCheck()` that currently skips key spans and failure cases.
