docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\raw\codex.stderr.log:6234:- The determinism contract is incomplete 
because it ignores validator-time behavior. `submitWithResult()` runs validators immediately with a live `World`, 
before the command is queued, so "route all input through `world.submit()`" is not enough unless validators are also 
required to be deterministic and side-effect free. As written, a user can follow 11 and still create uncaptured 
out-of-tick mutations. `docs/design/2026-04-26-session-recording-and-replay-design.md:396-408`; 
`src/world.ts:728-757,760-766`
docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-26\1\raw\codex.stderr.log:6247:- ADR 1, keeping session recording separate 
