docs\reviews\session-recording-spec\2026-04-27\2\diff.md:901:+**Decision:** `SessionBundle` is exported as a 
strict-JSON shared type and is identical regardless of producer. Both `SessionRecorder.toBundle()` and 
`scenarioCaptureToBundle()` emit the same shape; `MemorySink.toBundle()` and `FileSink.toBundle()` produce 
structurally equal bundles modulo `attachments[].ref` (dataUrl vs sidecar). Sidecar binary payloads live outside the 
JSON shape and are accessed via `source.readSidecar(id)`. The replayer accepts `SessionBundle` regardless of producer.
