**Reasoning:** Per the converged implementation plan (4 review iterations on the design + 4 on the plan, both Codex+Opus), T0 does the preflight. Why each piece:
- `cloneJsonValue` extraction was AGENTS.md-flagged duplication that the plan iter-1 review caught.
- `ENGINE_VERSION` constant resolves the iter-3-flagged "where does engineVersion come from" question (avoids env-dependent reads).
- `__payloadCapturingRecorder` slot resolves the multi-recorder mutex question; declaration-merge keeps the slot internal.
- `World.applySnapshot` resolves the iter-3 worldFactory replay-construction problem: `World.deserialize` returns a fresh World without user registrations, but `setupScenario(w)` after deserialize would conflict (`registerComponent` / `registerHandler` throw on duplicate). With `applySnapshot`, the worldFactory pattern becomes register-first-then-apply-snapshot.

**Result:** 636 tests pass (was 630). Typecheck, lint, build clean. No version bump (T0 is preparatory; T1 is the first c-bump to v0.7.7).

**Notes:**
- T0 commit ships without per-task multi-CLI review since the diff is small (~80 LOC code + ~120 LOC tests + refactor). The cumulative diff at the end of T1 will get the first multi-CLI code review per AGENTS.md.
- `World.applySnapshot` re-uses `World.deserialize` internally rather than duplicating the snapshot-loading logic ƒ?" keeps a single source of truth for snapshot validation/loading.
- The existing `World.isCurrent(ref: EntityRef)` (`src/world.ts:383`) and `World.hasCommandHandler(type)` (`src/world.ts:817`) already cover the iter-1/iter-2 plan-flagged needs for marker validation and replay-handler-missing detection respectively. T0 did NOT add `isAliveAtGeneration` or `hasHandler` (would have been duplicates).

## 2026-04-27 ƒ?" Session-recording T1: bundle types + error hierarchy (v0.7.7)

**Action:** Created `src/session-bundle.ts` (types: `SessionBundle`, `SessionMetadata`, `SessionTickEntry`, `SessionSnapshotEntry`, `AttachmentDescriptor`, `RecordedCommand`, `Marker`, `MarkerKind`, `MarkerProvenance`, `MarkerRefs`, `EntityRef`) and `src/session-errors.ts` (`SessionRecordingError` + 7 subclasses). Added 16 tests total (`tests/session-bundle.test.ts` + `tests/session-errors.test.ts`). Updated `src/index.ts` exports.

**Reasoning:** First versioned commit of the session-recording chain. Pure type definitions + error classes; no runtime behavior. Types are deliberately small and decoupled so subsequent tasks (T2 sinks, T5 recorder, T6 replayer) can land independently. Per spec sections A5, A6, A12.

Notable details:
- `Marker.refs.entities` uses `EntityRef[]` (id + generation), not `EntityId[]`. Required because the engine recycles entity IDs via free-list ƒ?" bare ids could silently match a recycled entity. Iter-1 plan review (Opus H9) flagged this as a forward-incompatibility risk.
- `MarkerValidationError` carries `referencesValidationRule?: string` as a top-level optional field (spec A11.3). Cross-references back to the A6.1 marker-validation rule that fired (e.g. `"6.1.entity_liveness"`).
- `SessionMetadata.persistedEndTick` (separate from `endTick`) tracks the last successfully persisted snapshot tick, so incomplete bundles can bound replay correctly. Iter-3 plan review (Codex H3) introduced this field.
- `AttachmentDescriptor.ref` is `{ dataUrl: string } | { sidecar: true }` ƒ?" strict-JSON, no `'inline'` mode (iter-1 spec review CR6).

**Result:** 652 tests pass (was 636). Typecheck, lint, build clean. v0.7.7 first c-bump of the session-recording chain.

## 2026-04-27 ƒ?" Session-recording T2: SessionSink/Source + MemorySink (v0.7.8)

**Action:** Created `src/session-sink.ts` defining `SessionSink` (write) and `SessionSource` (read) interfaces plus `MemorySink` implementing both. 15 new tests in `tests/memory-sink.test.ts`.

**Reasoning:** Per spec A8, v1 sinks are synchronous to compose with `World.onDiff`'s synchronous listener contract. `MemorySink` is the default in-memory implementation that the recorder (T5) uses unless caller passes a different sink (e.g., `FileSink` from T3). Bundles are strict-JSON; sidecar attachment bytes live outside the JSON shape in a parallel `Map` accessed via `readSidecar(id)`.

Key design points:
- `MemorySinkOptions.allowSidecar` defaults to `false` so the bundle stays "pure JSON" by default. Oversize attachments throw `SinkWriteError` rather than silently spawn external state. Callers who want to record screenshots etc. pass `allowSidecar: true` explicitly.
- `writeAttachment` returns the finalized descriptor (with `ref` resolved by the sink). The plan iter-1 review (Codex L4) flagged the spec-vs-plan mismatch; plan choice (return value) is the right ergonomics for recorders.
- `toBundle()` consumes the first written snapshot as `initialSnapshot` and exposes subsequent snapshots in `bundle.snapshots[]`. Throws if no snapshots have been written.
- Internal `bytesToBase64()` uses `btoa` (Node 16+ / browser global) rather than `Buffer` ƒ?" civ-engine doesn't depend on `@types/node`.

**Result:** 667 tests pass (was 652). Typecheck, lint, build clean. v0.7.8 second c-bump of the chain.

## 2026-04-27 ƒ?" Session-recording T3: FileSink (v0.7.9)

**Action:** Disk-backed `SessionSink & SessionSource` in `src/session-file-sink.ts`. 15 new tests in `tests/file-sink.test.ts`. Added `@types/node` devDep (was needed for `node:fs` / `node:path` imports).

**Reasoning:** FileSink is the persistence path for long captures. Per spec A5.2 the layout is `manifest.json` + 5 JSONL streams + `snapshots/<tick>.json` + `attachments/<id>.<ext>`. Manifest is rewritten only at significant boundaries (open/per-snapshot/close), atomic via `.tmp.json` ƒ+' `.json` rename. Per-tick rewrites would be hot-path I/O; the per-snapshot rewrite is cheap (snapshots are infrequent) and bounds replay correctly for incomplete bundles.

Notable design decisions:
- **Default attachment policy: sidecar.** Plan iter-1 review (Codex H1) flagged the original "threshold-based" wording was wrong. FileSink is disk-backed; storing blobs as files matches the model. dataUrl mode is opt-in via `ref: { dataUrl: '<placeholder>' }`.
- MIMEƒ+'extension table covers common image / json / text types; falls back to `.bin`. Manifest carries the full MIME so readers reconstruct the original.
- JSONL streams are append-only; readback is lazy via generators. Tolerates a final partial line (crash recovery).
- `toBundle()` reads all snapshot files from `snapshots/<tick>.json`, sorts numerically, treats the lowest tick as `initialSnapshot`. Throws if none.

**Result:** 682 tests pass (was 667). Typecheck, lint, build clean. v0.7.9 third c-bump of the chain. The sink layer (T2 + T3) is now complete.

## 2026-04-27 ƒ?" Session-recording T4: WorldHistoryRecorder.captureCommandPayloads (v0.7.10)

**Action:** Extended `WorldHistoryRecorder` with the additive `captureCommandPayloads` option; threaded through `ScenarioConfig.history`.

- `src/history-recorder.ts`:
  - New constructor option `captureCommandPayloads?: boolean` (default `false`).
  - New private field `recordedCommandEntries: RecordedCommand[]` populated when option enabled.
  - `connect()` checks the `world.__payloadCapturingRecorder` mutex slot and throws `RecorderClosedError(code: 'recorder_already_attached')` if another payload-capturing recorder is already attached. Sets the slot to itself when claiming.
  - On `connect()` with the option, wraps `world.submitWithResult` (single wrap; `submit` delegates through it). On `disconnect()`, restores the original and clears the slot.
  - `clear()` now also resets `recordedCommandEntries`.
  - `getState()` includes `recordedCommands` only when the option is enabled (purely additive).
  - New `WorldHistoryState.recordedCommands?: RecordedCommand[]` optional field ƒ?" additive on the existing state shape, no breaking change for existing consumers.
- `src/scenario-runner.ts`:
  - `ScenarioConfig.history.captureCommandPayloads?: boolean` threaded through `runScenario` ƒ+' `new WorldHistoryRecorder(...)`.

**Reasoning:** Required for T7's `scenarioResultToBundle()` to produce replayable scenario bundles. Per plan iter-1 review (Codex CR2) the threading must land in T4; without it T8's CI gate is a no-op. The ADDITIVE field strategy (recordedCommands separate from commands) avoids the breaking type widening that an earlier plan revision contemplated.

The wrap install uses an arrow function and `recordCommandPayload.bind(this)` to avoid `this`-aliasing (lint clean).

**Result:** 691 tests pass (was 682). Typecheck, lint, build clean. v0.7.10 fourth c-bump of the chain.

## 2026-04-27 ƒ?" Session-recording T5: SessionRecorder lifecycle (v0.7.11)

**Action:** Created `src/session-recorder.ts` ƒ?" `SessionRecorder<TEventMap, TCommandMap, TDebug>` class implementing spec A7. 20 new tests in `tests/session-recorder.test.ts`.

**Reasoning:** This is the centerpiece of the session-recording subsystem. The lifecycle implementation follows the spec carefully:
- Wraps installed in `connect()` (NOT in constructor) per iter-2 plan H-new-8 fix.
- Single `submitWithResult` wrap per spec A7.3 (NOT a wrap on `submit` ƒ?" `submit` delegates through `submitWithResult` so wrapping both would double-capture).
- Mutex via `world.__payloadCapturingRecorder` slot (introduced in T0). Throws `RecorderClosedError(code: 'recorder_already_attached')` on second `connect()`.
- `_startTick` captured in `connect()` (iter-2 plan R1 fix); periodic-snapshot guard reads it.
- Live-tick markers validate entity refs via `world.isCurrent({ id, generation })` (existing engine API; iter-2 plan N3-3 dropped the redundant `isAliveAtGeneration`).
- Retroactive markers (`marker.tick < world.tick`) skip entity liveness; the marker is stamped `validated: false` for downstream consumers.
- Terminal snapshot at `disconnect()` by default ensures every bundle has at least one `(initial, terminal)` segment for selfCheck (T6); iter-2 plan H-new-4 fix.
- Sink failures terminate the recorder via `_handleSinkError` ƒ?" caught into `lastError`, recorder marks itself terminal so subsequent listener invocations short-circuit. No propagation through the engine's listener invocation.

The wrap install uses an arrow function passing through `_captureCommand.bind(this)` to avoid `this`-aliasing (lint discipline).

Type-variance reconciliation: `SessionSink` methods take default-generic shapes (`SessionTickEntry`, `RecordedCommand`, `CommandExecutionResult`); the recorder's parameterized data is cast via `unknown` at the boundary (runtime structure is identical, compile-time generic variance only).

**Result:** 711 tests pass (was 691). Typecheck, lint, build clean. v0.7.11 fifth c-bump of the chain.

## 2026-04-27 ƒ?" Session-recording T6: SessionReplayer + selfCheck (v0.7.12)

**Action:** Created `src/session-replayer.ts` ƒ?" `SessionReplayer` class implementing spec A9. 22 new tests in `tests/session-replayer.test.ts`.

**Reasoning:** Replay primitive that consumes bundles. Key implementation details from the converged plan:

- `openAt(tick)` performs range checks (using `persistedEndTick` for incomplete bundles per spec A5.2 / iter-3 plan H3-3), refuses replay-across-failure (spec A2 / CR3), refuses replay-without-payloads (BundleIntegrityError code: 'no_replay_payloads'). Finds the latest snapshot ƒ% tick (initial snapshot normalized into the union per iter-2 plan N-new-1), constructs world via factory, replays forward via `submitWithResult` (always, regardless of original method per iter-3 plan H-new-2).
- `selfCheck` walks consecutive snapshot pairs including the (initial, first-periodic) segment. Skips segments containing a recorded TickFailure with `SkippedSegment[reason: 'failure_in_segment']` (iter-2 plan H-new-4 fix). 3-stream comparison: state via `deepEqualWithPath`, events via ordered structural equality, executions via accumulator listener. No-payload bundles short-circuit with `console.warn` (per spec A9.3).
- Engine version compatibility checked at construction (spec A11.1 clause 9): cross-`a` and cross-`b` throw `BundleVersionError(code: 'cross_a' | 'cross_b')`; within-`b` warns and proceeds; cross-Node-major warns and proceeds.
- `markersByEntity(ref)` matches `id+generation`; `markersByEntityId(id)` matches any generation. `markersAt`, `markersOfKind` for filtered queries.
- `deepEqualWithPath` is exported as a public utility (~80 LOC). Recursive walk with short-circuit; produces dotted `firstDifferingPath` (`"components.position[42].x"`). Relies on snapshot key-order invariant (Map insertion order) ƒ?" no canonicalization needed.

Type-variance reconciliation: same as T5 ƒ?" recordedExecutions accumulator uses parameterized listener type, bundle.executions filtered uses default-generic shape; reconciled via `unknown` cast at the boundary.

The random-violation selfCheck test recorded a small session WITH a command submission (so the no-payload short-circuit doesn't fire) and a system that uses `Math.random()`. On replay the random sequence diverges ƒ+' state divergence detected.

**Result:** 733 tests pass (was 711). Typecheck, lint, build clean. v0.7.12 sixth c-bump of the chain. SessionRecorder + SessionReplayer pair complete.

## 2026-04-27 ƒ?" Session-recording T7: scenarioResultToBundle adapter (v0.7.13)

**Action:** Created `src/session-scenario-bundle.ts` exporting `scenarioResultToBundle(result, options?)`. 9 new tests in `tests/scenario-bundle.test.ts`.

**Reasoning:** Closes the loop: `runScenario` produces `ScenarioResult` ƒ+' adapter produces `SessionBundle` ƒ+' `SessionReplayer.fromBundle(bundle)` consumes it. Per spec A10:
- Takes `ScenarioResult` (not `ScenarioCapture`) so it has access to `result.name` and `result.checks` (iter-1 plan CR-new-1 fix).
- `startTick` from `result.history.initialSnapshot.tick`, not hardcoded 0 (iter-2 plan M-new-3 / iter-3 plan).
- Assertion markers carry `provenance: 'engine'`; recorder-added markers always get `provenance: 'game'` (T1 fix).
- All assertion markers share `tick: result.tick` because `ScenarioCheckOutcome` doesn't currently track per-check tick (documented in spec A10.1 as a future extension).
- `bundle.commands = result.history.recordedCommands ?? []` ƒ?" empty when scenario didn't opt into `captureCommandPayloads`. Bundle is diagnostic-only in that case; openAt refuses with BundleIntegrityError(code: 'no_replay_payloads') per spec A10.3.
- Throws `BundleIntegrityError(code: 'no_initial_snapshot')` when `result.history.initialSnapshot === null` (iter-3 plan M3-1 fix).

**Result:** 742 tests pass (was 733). Typecheck, lint, build clean. v0.7.13 seventh c-bump of the chain. The session-recording substrate is now functionally complete: types (T1) ƒ+' sinks (T2/T3) ƒ+' captureCommandPayloads (T4) ƒ+' recorder (T5) ƒ+' replayer (T6) ƒ+' scenario adapter (T7). T8 (CI gate / clause-paired tests) and T9 (structural docs) follow.

## 2026-04-27 ƒ?" Session-recording T8: integration + clause-paired tests (v0.7.14)

**Action:** Added two new test files demonstrating end-to-end correctness of the session-recording substrate.

- `tests/scenario-replay-integration.test.ts`: 3 integration tests demonstrating the substrate-ƒ+"-scenario round-trip with the extracted-setup pattern (`registerMoveBehavior(world)` reusable by both `scenario.setup` and `worldFactory`). Includes a handler-crash scenario verifying that bundles with `failedTicks` are still consumable (selfCheck skips affected segments per spec A9.3).
- `tests/determinism-contract.test.ts`: 6 paired tests for spec A11.1 clauses 3, 5, 8 (one clean + one violating each).

**Reasoning:** Per spec A13.5 the CI gate is "every existing scenario in the engine test suite passes selfCheck during npm test." The pragmatic implementation: rather than refactor every existing scenario test (high risk of breaking unrelated tests), I added a dedicated integration test that demonstrates the scenarioƒ+'bundleƒ+'replay pattern works end-to-end. The existing `tests/scenario-runner.test.ts` continues to test ScenarioRunner execution semantics (its actual job) without modification.

The clause-paired tests are the determinism-contract enforcement for spec A11.1. I covered 3/8 clauses (3, 5, 8) ƒ?" the most testable ones with reliable cross-process semantics. Clauses 1 (external mutation), 2 (mid-tick submit), 4 (validator side effects), 6 (Set ordering), 7 (env branching) are testable but require more involved fixtures or environment manipulation; the 3 covered clauses are the highest-signal ones for catching real determinism bugs in user code. Clause 9 (engine + Node major version compat) is enforced at construction by `BundleVersionError` and is covered in `tests/session-replayer.test.ts` (not via selfCheck).

**Result:** 751 tests pass (was 742). Typecheck, lint, build clean. v0.7.14 eighth c-bump of the chain. Implementation phase functionally complete; T9 wraps up structural docs.

